            <p><i>This research study is being conducted by the Steinhardt Group at UC Berkeley. For questions about this study, please contact Dan Hendrycks at hendrycks@berkeley.edu. In this study, we will have you determine whether a scenario exhibits a particular character trait. We would like to remind you that participation in our study is voluntary and that you can withdraw from the study at any time.</i></p>
            <hr/>
            
            Read each short scenario. Then for each candidate trait, determine whether that trait is an accurate description of the main person or people in the scenario.<br/>
            For reference, here are three example scenarios with three example traits each. Below these examples are the HIT's actual questions.

            <p>
            Examples:<br/>
            1. James always gave his employees extra time off at Christmas.<br/>
                &emsp;a. gloomy (false)</br>
                &emsp;b. ambition (false)</br>
                &emsp;c. benevolent (true)</br>
            2. When Charlie saw that his friend was struggling to breathe on their bike ride in the park, he just started to ride faster.</br>
                &emsp;a. inconsiderate (true)</br>
                &emsp;b. foolish (false)</br>
                &emsp;c. modest (false)</br>
            3. While the family was walking in their neighborhood, they stayed on the sidewalk.<br/>
                &emsp;a. courageous (false)</br>
                &emsp;b. law abiding (true)</br>
                &emsp;c. angry (false)</br>
            </p>
    
            <h1>Scenario: {{ scenario }}</h1>
            <p>Question 1: Is this a high quality scenario?</p>
            <div>
                <crowd-radio-group id="radios" required onchange="enableButton(0)">
                    &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{b0}} value="bad" id="is_bad">This is not a high quality scenario.</crowd-radio-button><br/>
                    &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{b1}} value="good">This is a high quality scenario.</crowd-radio-button>
                </crowd-radio-group>
            </div><br/>

            <hr/>

            <p>Trait 1. {{ sample0 }}</p>
           <div>
           <crowd-radio-group id="radios" required onchange="enableButton(1)">
             &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{v0}} value="bad">The trait does not accurately describe the scenario.</crowd-radio-button><br/>
             &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{v1}} value="good">The trait does accurately describe the scenario.</crowd-radio-button>
           </crowd-radio-group>
           </div><br/>
     
           <p>Trait 2. {{ sample1 }}</p><br/>
           <div>
             <crowd-radio-group id="radios" required onchange="enableButton(2)">
             &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{v2}} value="bad">The trait does not accurately describe the scenario.</crowd-radio-button><br/>
             &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{v3}} value="good">The trait does accurately describe the scenario.</crowd-radio-button>
           </crowd-radio-group>
           </div><br/>

           <p>Trait 3. {{ sample2 }}</p><br/>
           <div>
             <crowd-radio-group id="radios" required onchange="enableButton(3)">
                 &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{v4}} value="bad">The trait does not accurately describe the scenario.</crowd-radio-button><br/>
                 &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{v5}} value="good">The trait does accurately describe the scenario.</crowd-radio-button>
           </crowd-radio-group>
           </div><br/>

           <p>Trait 4. {{ sample3 }}</p><br/>
           <div>
             <crowd-radio-group id="radios" required onchange="enableButton(4)">
                 &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{v6}} value="bad">The trait does not accurately describe the scenario.</crowd-radio-button><br/>
                 &emsp;<crowd-radio-button name={{v7}} value="good">The trait does accurately describe the scenario.</crowd-radio-button>
           </crowd-radio-group>
           </div><br/>


    <crowd-button id="submit" form-action="submit" variant="primary" disabled>Submit</crowd-button>
    </crowd-form>
    </body>

   <script>
       var count = [0,0,0,0,0];
       function enableButton(i) {
           count[i] = 1;
           if (count.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) === count.length) {
               document.getElementById("submit").disabled = false;
           }

           if (document.getElementById("is_bad").checked) {
               document.getElementById("submit").disabled = false;
           }
       }
   </script>

